{"000-section": {"000-title": "MP Sanjeevani Clinics (Mohalla Clinic) \u2013 Free Treatment & 120 Types of Medicines"}, "001-section": {"000-title": "MP govt. to open 208 Sanjeevani Clinics in rural & urban areas, free OPD, checkup of pregnant women, vaccination, treatment & medicines on lines of mohalla clinic in Delhi"}, "002-section": {"000-title": "MP Sanjeevani Clinic (Mohalla Clinics)", "001-normal": "The state govt. of Madhya Pradesh will open MP Sanjeevani Clinics in around 208 locations to provide affordable and quality healthcare services to people. At these Sanjivani Clinics, there would be a facility of general consultation (OPD), checkup of pregnant women, vaccination and treatment of communicable diseases.", "002-normal": "These Sanjeevani Clinics will also provide treatment for contagious diseases including cancer, high blood pressure and diabetes. At the MP Sanjeevani Clinics, there would be free checkup for around 68 types of diseases. Moreover, around 120 types of medicines would be provided absolutely free of cost to poor people."}, "003-section": {"000-title": "Sanjeevani Express Yojana", "001-normal": "To ensure better healthcare facilities, MP govt. had already started replacement of old vehicles under Janani Express (\u091c\u0928\u0928\u0940 \u090f\u0915\u094d\u0938\u092a\u094d\u0930\u0947\u0938) and Sanjivani Express Yojana (\u0938\u0902\u091c\u0940\u0935\u0928\u0940 \u090f\u0915\u094d\u0938\u092a\u094d\u0930\u0947\u0938 \u092f\u094b\u091c\u0928\u093e). More than 45 ambulances were made out of services due to their deteriorating condition and new vehicles are being put in place. CM Kamal Nath had earlier flag off 45 ambulances under Janani Express Scheme.", "002-normal": "The main objective of these 2 schemes is to regularly improve the quality of basic facilities being provided to poor people. Any person must not be deprived of basic healthcare services and there must be no division on the basis of their caste, colour and religion.", "003-normal": "As per the official reports, there are 737 Sanjeevani and 108 Janani Ambulances currently functional in 51 districts of Madhya Pradesh. These vehicles have already travelled more than 2 lakh 50 thousand kilometers. Furthermore, the state govt. is going to replace 50 old vehicles which are more than 5 years old with the new ones.", "004-normal": "Source / Reference Link: https://aajtak.intoday.in/story/mohalla-clinics-madhya-pradesh-chief-minister-kamal-nath-medical-facilities-sanjeevani-clinics-1-1143979.html"}}